{"questionId": "ceb2e234-3ab3-4376-b66a-cf8535278d77_4", "correctAnswer": "13", "section": "Math", "steps": [{"title": "Substitute the value x = 36", "content": "Replace $x$ with $36$ in $$f(x) = 7 + \\sqrt{x}.$$ This gives $$f(36) = 7 + \\sqrt{36}.$$"}, {"title": "Compute the result", "content": "Simplify: $$f(36) = 7 + 6 = 13.$$ The answer is <strong>13</strong>."}]}